<font color="#FF0000">PHOTO RECON VFP-63, ORISKANY</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  3 19:00:48 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
NAVY PHOTO RECONNAISANCE and PHOTO INTELLIGENCE boys in the TONKIN GULF YACHT CLUB (1967-68). Damnit, I've lost contact with all of them. VFP-63 det Golf, U.S.S. Oriskany (CVA-34), West Pac Cruise to Vietnam. <br>
Big Ern killed himself in 1973. It took me by surprise. He was teaching inner city high school in Kansas City; went to his summer cabin near Shawano, Wisconsin and wasted himself. No explanation. No note. You big dope, I loved you.<br>
Where are the rest of you guys? Bob Andrise. I can't find you in the North Carolina directory. Joe Dietrich of Flint, Michigan. Richard Adam. Harry Hebb. It would be great to talk to you again. Remember the day the Forrestal blew up and killed 120 men? As I was swabbing out shrapnel craters the poor S.O.B.s kept asking, &quot;What are doing here? Just what the hell is this all about?&quot;<br>
Three years ago, in Grant Park, Chicago, I watched an old Vietnamese gentleman shuffling along the waterfront. Dragging a foot as result of an injury suffered perhaps long ago, in that other land, I thought to myself: &quot;It could have been from one of my bombs.&quot;<br>
I felt a strange kind of kinship to the elder Asian but I also felt very sad and ashamed. My eyes overflowed with tears. <br>
God, have I changed.
